      "analogy": "Think of buying from a vending machine watched by a stadium full of referees. You insert your coins (sign a transaction), the referees all independently agree the machine did exactly the right thing (consensus), and the sale is stamped permanently onto a giant scoreboard that everyone in the world can read forever.",
