          "title": "Approve and sign in your wallet",
          "plain": "Your wallet pops up asking you to confirm. You're signing with your secret key to prove the request is genuinely from you.",
          "detail": "If spending an ERC-20, an approve or Permit2 signature may be required first. The swap transaction is then signed locally (EIP-712 or legacy) so the private key never leaves the device.",
